# Firestore Rules

- All collections are top-level (books, chapters, sections, contentBlocks, users, etc.).
- Every section supports unlimited content blocks with a `type` and `order` field.
- Use ISO string timestamps for `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.
- Slug fields must be URL-safe and unique within their parent scope.
- Service functions in `src/services/` are the only place for Firestore queries.
- Hooks in `src/hooks/` wrap services with TanStack Query.
- Document any schema changes in `docs/DATABASE.md`.
- Deploy index changes via `firestore.indexes.json`.
